{{Infobox factory | name = ACS Mersin <!-- Commented out: | image = FormerStThomasAssemblyPlant.jpg --> | alt = | caption = | location_map= Turkey | built = {{Start date|1969}} | location = [[Mersin]], Turkey | coordinates = {{coord|36|51|50|N|34|06|43|E}} | industry = [[Glass]] | products = | employees = 461 | architect = | style = | area = | volume = | address = Yenitaşkent, Mersin, Turkey | defunct = }} '''ACS Mersin''' is the name of a glass factory in [[Mersin]], [[Turkey]]. ACS stands for ''Anadolu Cam Sanayii'' ("Anatolian Glass Industry")
The factory is at {{coord|36|51|50|N|34|06|43|E}} in Yenitaşkent neighborhood to the north of the Turkish state highway {{TUR-D|400}} which connects Mersin to [[Tarsus, Mersin|Tarsus]]. Its distance to Mersin is about {{convert|13|km}}.
The factory was put into operation in 1969. In 1975, it was acquired by Şişecam Group of Companies.<ref>[http://www.sisecam.com.tr/tr/hakkimizda/tarihce ACS history]</ref> In 1988 NNPB (narrow neck press and blow) technology was successfully used for the first time in Turkey at ACS.<ref>[http://www.sisecam.com.tr/en/business-segments/glass-packaging Şişecam page]</ref> Current annual glass production is 260 822 metric tons. The number of employees is 461. But after the planned instauration the annual production will rise to 366685 metric tons and the number of employees will increase to 483.<ref>[http://guneygazetesi.com/m/news.php?id=7891 Güney newspaper {{tr icon}}]</ref>
